    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: The guide's content is informational and code-based, not data-driven, so traditional charts are unsuitable. Instead, information is presented using styled tables and code blocks for clarity. The key 'visualizations' are interactive demos: 1) A CSS slider to demonstrate the 'border-radius' property in real-time, making the concept tangible. 2) A live implementation of the guide's JavaScript example, allowing users to click a button and see DOM manipulation happen. This direct interaction is the most effective way to teach behavior. All elements are built with HTML/CSS/JS, confirming no SVG/Mermaid is used. -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
